Senior/Manager, Project Pursuit - SEAT (SEAT/201311/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00005820
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Nov 7 2013
Job Level
Supervisor / Manager
|
Responsibilities:
Define business drivers and opportunities for cross divisional growth in SEAT Project Pursuit.
Identify and lead Key Projects to ensure focus, strategy and action plans are in place.
Work closely with in-country project pursuit team in SEAT destination EPCs projects.
Engage with GP3 team to pursue international projects destination for SEAT.
Leverage and engage regional/global capabilities and/or resources to support pursuit activities.
Maintain effective communication and coordination of EMR cross-divisional project pursuit including PATT usage.
Requirements:
Diploma/Degree in an Engineering or Chemical discipline; minimum 5 to 8 years of relevant experience in Sales preferably in the Oil & Gas, Refining and Chemicals.
Strong business management and customer orientation; with financial and commercial knowledge.
Critical Competencies required: Drive for Results, Dealing with Ambiguity, Business Acumen & Interpersonal Savvy.
Excellent interpersonal, communication and negotiation skills.
Working experience with EPCs and Solutions Selling will have an added advantage.